-- Springer CEO, Deutsche's Jain Germany's Best-Paid Managers, Magazine Says
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-06-25T08:57:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/springer-ceo-deutsche-s-jain-germany-s-best-paid-managers-magazine-says.html

          
          
             Axel Springer AG Chief Executive
Officer Mathias Doepfner was Germany’s top-paid manager last
year, earning about 11 million euros, Manager-Magazin reported,
citing research it carried out in cooperation with management
professor Joachim Schwalbach of Berlin’s Humboldt University.  
 Second on the list is Deutsche Bank AG’s Anshu Jain, who
heads the investment banking unit and joined the bank’s
management board in April, 2009. Jain earned an estimated 10.3
million euros on an annualized basis, more than Chief Executive
Officer Josef Ackermann, who was paid 9.4 million euros, the
magazine reported.  
          
          


  


        